%N A393636 Decimal expansion of 2*cos(Pi/8)/(1+cos(Pi/8)).
%C A393636 Linear approximation of the type |h|=alpha*max(|x|,|y|)+beta*min(|x|,|y|) to the hypot function |h|=sqrt(x^2+y^2) attains the smallest maximum error when alpha is this constant and beta = A393637. The absolute value of the minimax error of this approximation equals A393638.
%H A393636 Ara Abdulsatar Assim, <a href="https://doi.org/10.18721/JCSTCS.14401">ASIC implementation of high-speed vector magnitude & arctangent approximator</a>, Computing, Telecommunication and Control, 14 (2021), 7-14.
%H A393636 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpha_max_plus_beta_min_algorithm">Alpha max plus beta min algorithm</a>.
%F A393636 Equals 2/(1 + 2/sqrt(2 + sqrt(2))). - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Feb 24 2026
%e A393636 0.960433870103419965...
%t A393636 RealDigits[2/(1 + 2/Sqrt[2 + Sqrt[2]]), 10, 105][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Feb 24 2026 *)
